The paper discusses a method for detecting hidden messages in DNA using deep recurrent neural networks, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of neural networks for classification and sequence learning suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of RNNs, which is a common technique in the field of natural language processing (cs.NE), suggesting that this category may also be relevant.
